 electric company from march  to october   his responsibilities included a broad range of utility operations as well as focusing on developing the workforce skills and workplace culture needed for dte electric to be successful in a changing utility environment he served as the chief operating officer at dte energy company from march  to october   and served as its chief executive officer from  to october   previously he served as the president at dte energy company from march  to august  mr earley served as the president and chief operating officer of dte gas company until july   he served as the president and chief operating officer of long island lighting company an electric and gas utility in new york from  to  he held several other positions at long island lighting including executive vice president and general counsel he joined lilco in  from the law firm of hunton  williams where he was a partner as a member of long islands energy and environmental team he had participated in the licensing of both nuclear and nonnuclear generating plants and represented a substantial number of nuclear utilities in rulemaking actions before the nuclear regulatory commission he served as chairman of pge corporation from september   to march   mr earley served as an officer in the united states navy nuclear submarine program where he was qualified as a chief engineer officer he served as an executive chairman of dte energy company from september  to september   he serves as the chairman of united way for southeastern michigan he served as the chairman of edison electric institute inc and served as a first vice at edison electric institute he was directly involved in the development of national policies on energy the environment and climate change issues he also served as chair of nuclear energy institute and worked to revitalize the nuclear industry in the united states he served as the chairman of the board at henry ford health system inc he served as the chairman of detroit renaissance mr earley has been an independent director of ford motor company since march  he has been a director of pge corporation since september   he serves as a director of business leaders for michigan he serves as a director of electric power research institute inc he has been a director of pacific gas and electric company since june  he serves as a director of nuclear energy institute mr earley serves as a director of detroit renaissance he serves on the listed member advisory board for the new york stock exchange he serves as a director of mutual of america capital management llc he served as a director of masco corporation until may   and previously served as an independent director from  to august  he served as a director of edison electric institute inc he served as a director of dte energy company from  to september   and comerica incorporated from july  to february   he served as a director of dte electric company he served as a director of plug power inc from june  to november   mr earley served as a director of comerica bank from  to july  he served as a director of invest detroit he is a director of community foundation for southeastern michigan and cornerstone schools detroit zoological society he is a director of business roundtable he serves on the boards of numerous charitable and civic organizations including united way of the bay area bay area council san francisco committee on jobs and the exploratorium mr earley is a trustee of many community and professional organizations he serves on the department of energys electricity advisory board and the advisory board for the college of engineering for the university of notre dame his community service has also been recognized by the detroit news and in  he was selected as one of several michiganians of the year mr earley earned a bachelor of science degree in physics a master of science degree in engineering and a law degree at the university of notre dameread full background corporate headquarters  be