lso proxies must disclose specific detailed information regarding the pay practices for certain executives       privacy policy terms of use about us contact us  salarycom all rights reserved us salaries canadian salaries purchase a salary report salaries by category salaries by income salaries by industry popular salaries negotiation tips benefits calculator search job openings job openings by state job openings by category education by career education by level education by major cost of living calculator pge names anthony f earley jr as ceo  sfgate subscribe sign in menusections httpwwwsfgatecombusinessarticlepgenamesanthonyfearleyjrasceophp pge names anthony f earley jr as ceo pge by david r baker published  am tuesday august   photo pge image of captionclose image  of  pges new chief executive officer president and chairman of the board anthony f earley jr pges new chief executive officer president and chairman of the board anthony f earley jr photo pge pge names anthony f earley jr as ceo    back to gallery pge corp on monday named as its new ceo anthony f earley jr a veteran powerindustry executive credited with steering detroits electric utility through the largest blackout in american history earley  will replace peter darbee who stepped down in april in an effort to help pge and its subsidiary pacific gas and electric co recover from a series of crises including last years fatal pipeline explosion in san bruno earleys appointment marks the first time that pge has picked a new chief executive from outside the companys ranks for more than a decade earley served as chief executive officer of dte energy parent company of detroit edison and michigan consolidated gas co he gave up the ceo post last year but remained executive chairman of the companys board his career also includes leadership stints with a utility trade group and a nuclear power association pge has a proud legacy earley said in a prepared statement its a great privilege to help an iconic company recover from its recent challenges and reclaim its standing as the utility others admire and aspire to follow latest business videos trained as an engineer earley led dte at the time of the august  blackout that cut power to an estimated  million people in canada and eight northeastern states michigan officials praised his response earley held seven press conferences in the first three days after the blackout detailing the steps being taken to restore power and asking all customers who did have electricity to conserve power until the crisis was over tony earley proved that he was a leader we could rely on to be open honest and accountable at a very difficult time said former michigan gov jennifer granholm in a statement released by pge he stepped up publicly he made sure we knew what was happening what we could expect and when we could expect it and he made sure dte came through and delivered on what it promised his crisis management skills will be tested in his new role pge which serves  million people in northern and central california has struggled through a series of controversies over the past year a pgebacked ballot initiative last year that would have limited the ability of local governments to enter the public power business failed at the polls and angered much of the states political establishment the companys  billion smartmeter program prompted a customer backlash against the new wireless meters which some people consider a health risk and on sept  a pge natural gas pipeline exploded in san bruno killing eight people and leveling a neighborhood subsequent government investigations revealed flawed welds on the line that ruptured and shoddy recordkeeping on the companys vast network of pipes pge has already spent  million responding to the blast and costs could top  billion by years end pge customers want someone who can deliver safety and results said mindy spatt spokeswoman for the utility reform network consumer group it remains to be seen if he can deliver earley received degrees in physics engineering and law from the university of notre dame and has spent most of his life in the energy industry that stands in contrast to darbee a former investment banker who held positions at goldman sachs salomon brothers att and pacific bell before joining pge earley formerly served as chairman of both the edison electric institute a utility trade association and the nuclear energy institute the main lobbying group for the nuclear industry he also served as an officer in the us navys nuclear submarine program email david r baker at dbakersfchroniclecom latest from the sfgate homepageclick below for the top news from around the bay area and beyond sign up for our newsletters to be the first to learn about breaking news and more go to sign in and manage profile at the top of the page the trump presidency trump fires off volley of angry early morning tweets trump claims he has complete power to pardon trump commissions uss gerald r ford latest news berkeley man gets  years to life for human trafficking golfer shoots lowest score ever at major championship streetscape improvements bad for business sf merchants say  local spots may join national historic register more americans renting than any time in last  years richmond mayor witnessed attack outside bart station oakland man charged with attempt to support terrorist group sf stabbing victim idd as yearold city resident  american towns you havent heard of but should visit asap our favorite mustsee small towns in northern california  great bay area hikes that end with a beer  spots where bay area kids can experience the great outdoors all the things bay area athletes should do before they die the coolest thing to do in each bay area city seattle wilderness getaway among worlds most expensive this couple gave up their sf apartments to travel in a van how the pony express linked an isolated sf to the country barbary coast raid brought sf’s bad old days to an end todays top picks gam